    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application maintains a top-down, single-page dashboard for intuitive navigation. The "Overview" section is enhanced with a comprehensive, visually mapped sales funnel that precisely mirrors the user's provided diagram, incorporating specific stages like 'Email Venta' and a detailed 'Remarketing' loop. This funnel serves as the central interactive navigation hub. A "Customer Roadmap" section explicitly details the customer journey, linking directly to Impromax's actions. The four core funnel stages (Attraction, Consideration, Conversion, Loyalty) have been significantly expanded to include granular details on Google Ads, Meta Ads, and Brevo (email marketing) campaigns, product focus, and budget allocation strategies. This structure provides a holistic view, combining high-level navigation with in-depth tactical information for each stage, tailored to Impromax's specific products and sales goals. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Sales Goal & Budget Recommendation -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Key Metric Cards, Summary Text. Justification: Provides immediate high-level context.
        - Report Info: Budget Splits (Google/Meta) -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Interactive Donut Charts (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Tooltips on hover provide exact percentages. Justification: Donut charts are ideal for showing parts of a whole, making budget allocation instantly clear.
        - Report Info: Funnel Stages & Remarketing Loop (from provided image) -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Viz: Custom HTML/CSS Block-and-Line Funnel Diagram with clearly labeled steps, including specific email stages and a distinct 'Remarketing' branch with dynamic connections -> Interaction: Clickable segments scroll to the relevant detailed section. Justification: Directly translates the user's visual request into an interactive, structured flow, showing the core sales journey and the remarketing strategy as a loop. This is crucial for user understanding of the complex flow.
        - Report Info: Customer Journey -> Goal: Inform/Organize -> Viz: Interconnected Cards with HTML/CSS elements (like lines/arrows) for flow -> Interaction: Static, clear presentation. Justification: Visually clarifies the customer's progression and Impromax's corresponding actions.
        - Report Info: Detailed Campaign Strategies (Google Ads, Meta Ads, Brevo Email, CRO) per Funnel Stage -> Goal: Inform/Organize -> Viz: Detailed Text Blocks within styled cards, organized into collapsible/expandable sections for clarity -> Interaction: Static text, but organized for easy consumption. Justification: Provides the necessary granular detail for implementation without overwhelming the user on initial view.
        - Report Info: Products to Promote -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Lists within relevant campaign sections. Justification: Integrates product focus directly into tactical plans.
        - Report Info: Tools -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Styled Text Blocks. Justification: Simple, clean presentation of required tools.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
